title: Arizona’s Top Races Await Final Results in a Tension-Filled Election
description: Senator Mark Kelly, a Democrat, holds an edge in his bid for re-election, but the race for governor appears to be a true tossup, even as several Republican candidates sow doubts about the results.
dc:creator: Jazmine Ulloa and Jack Healy
media:credit: Alisha Jucevic for The New York Times
media:description: Ballots being processed this week at the Maricopa County Elections Center in Phoenix. All four of the state’s top races were uncalled as of midday Friday.
